title: Dye Process Book, Nippon hand weaves in "Kusakizome" dyes: handbook of Japanese weaves in natural plant dyes, 1959
title_raw: Nippon hand weaves in "Kusakizome" dyes: handbook of Japanese weaves in natural plant dyes
description: Book, covered with fabric, showing silk handwoven swatches dyed with plants and grasses, known as kusaki-zome. Lined with stenciled paper. Book is No. 35 from a limited edition of 200.

tombstone.epitaph: Dye Process Book, Nippon hand weaves in "Kusakizome" dyes: handbook of Japanese weaves in natural plant dyes, 1959; Written by Akira Yamazaki (Japanese, b. 1892); Japan; paper, silk; H x W: 28.5 × 20.5 cm (11 1/4 × 8 1/16 in.); Gift of Elizabeth Gordon; 1964-24-3
